  "text": "This section presents one particular effective diffusion strategy to solve LMS distributed estimation problems, see [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] for a detailed presentation. Here we focus on the Adapt-Then-Combine (ATC) strategy. The Adapt-Then-Combine (ATC) strategy aims at solving the problem of a scalar least mean squares linear regression over a sensor network. Observations y n (i) are assumed to arrive sequentially at consecutive instants i. In the usual setting [CITATION_3] , each sensor records both a noisy scalar measurement y n (i) ∈ R and a set of coefficients x n (i) under the assumption",
